{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "notes": [
    "v1 starter set: 5 real, freely-licensed AcroForm government forms (IRS W-9/W-4/1040/4506-T, USCIS I-9). This is NOT the >=25-of-top-100 target from P0-08's original acceptance criteria - see tasks/escalations/E-005-corpus-acquisition-gap.md and docs/specs/corpus-plan.md.",
    "Files are NOT duplicated here: 'file' paths point at the same binaries already stored under Fixtures/pdf-corpus/starter/ (these 5 forms serve double duty as both corpus and forms fixtures in this starter set), avoiding a second LFS-tracked copy of identical bytes.",
    "field_name values were extracted with Apple PDFKit (authoring-time inspection tool only, not PDFium/DocEngineHost - see Fixtures/pdf-corpus/README.md) by walking each page's widget annotations. They are the PDF's real AcroForm field names, not invented.",
    "vault_path values are PROPOSED canonical paths following the dot-separated-lowercase convention (root CLAUDE.md SS5). Schemas/vault-schema.yml is still empty pending P0-09 (Vault API package); these mappings are NOT yet ratified in a canonical catalog and must be reconciled with docs/specs/vault-schema.md once P0-09 lands (may require renaming, not structural rework).",
    "vault_path is null for fields that are not user-identity data at all (e.g. a requester's own address, an employer-completed field, a computed tax amount) - those are out of scope for vault-sourced autofill and are noted as such.",
    "Coverage is deliberately partial, not exhaustive: for large multi-page forms (1040) only the identity/filing-status/address header section is mapped in v1; income computation lines are not vault-sourced data and are out of scope. USCIS I-9 Section 2 (employer's List A/B/C document verification) depends on a runtime choice of which document the employee presented and needs FillPlanner-level logic, not a static manifest row - deferred."
  ],
